Build a Node Express Rest Api to handle the uses cases.

Create a rest api using Express.js that handles the requests based on the endpoints.
Create a MySQL database.
Create a task table and add the columns in respect to the sample task object below.

Endpoint ----------------------- Http Method -------- Description
taskApiUrl/tasks ---------------- post ----------------A user wants to save a new task.
taskApiUrl/tasks/:task_id --------get -----------------A user wants to get a specific task from DB.

Sample Task Object: 
{
"id" : "123123",
"title" : "this is title",
"description" : "lorem ipsum", 
"project_id" : "1357",
"due_date" : "2016-04-23",
"status" : "new"
}
